  "prompt": "What are the all time best hollywood movies?",
  "response": "Here's a list of some of the all-time best Hollywood movies, widely acclaimed and beloved by audiences and critics alike:\n\n1. **Citizen Kane (1941)**\n   - Directed by Orson Welles, this film is often cited as one of the greatest films ever made due to its innovative narrative structure and groundbreaking cinematography.\n\n2. **The Godfather (1972)**\n   - Directed by Francis Ford Coppola, this epic crime saga about the Corleone family is a landmark in American cinema.\n\n3. **The Godfather Part II (1974)**\n   - Also directed by Francis Ford Coppola, this sequel is often considered even better than the original, weaving together two parallel stories.\n\n4. **Casablanca (1942)**\n   - Directed by Michael Curtiz, this timeless romantic drama set during World War II features iconic performances and unforgettable lines.\n\n5. **Gone with the Wind (1939)**\n   - Directed by Victor Fleming, this epic historical romance is renowned for its sweeping narrative and grand production.\n\n6. **Schindler's List (1993)**\n   - Directed by Steven Spielberg, this powerful Holocaust drama won multiple Oscars and is celebrated for its emotional depth and historical accuracy.\n\n7. **The Shawshank Redemption (1994)**\n   - Directed by Frank Darabont, this inspiring story of hope and friendship in a prison setting has become a beloved classic.\n\n8. **Pulp Fiction (1994)**\n   - Directed by Quentin Tarantino, this groundbreaking film revitalized the crime genre with its nonlinear storytelling and eclectic soundtrack.\n\n9. **The Dark Knight (2008)**\n   - Directed by Christopher Nolan, this superhero film is often hailed as one of the best of its genre, thanks to its compelling narrative and Heath Ledger's iconic performance as the Joker.\n\n10. **Forrest Gump (1994)**\n    - Directed by Robert Zemeckis, this heartwarming story follows the life of Forrest Gump, who witnesses several defining historical events in the 20th century.\n\n11. **Star Wars (1977)**\n    - Directed by George Lucas, this space opera revolutionized the film industry and spawned a massive franchise.\n\n12. **The Wizard of Oz (1939)**\n    - Directed by Victor Fleming, this beloved musical fantasy is famous for its colorful characters and memorable songs.\n\n13. **One Flew Over the Cuckoo's Nest (1975)**\n    - Directed by Milos Forman, this drama set in a mental institution features unforgettable performances and a gripping storyline.\n\n14. **Lawrence of Arabia (1962)**\n    - Directed by David Lean, this epic biographical adventure is celebrated for its stunning cinematography and epic scope.\n\n15. **The Silence of the Lambs (1991)**\n    - Directed by Jonathan Demme, this psychological thriller won multiple Oscars and is known for its chilling performances and suspenseful plot.\n\nThese films are just a selection of the many great movies Hollywood has produced over the years, and they are considered classics for their storytelling, direction, and cultural impact.",
